nts1.d: Renowned Italian soundtrack composer Fabio Frizzi, famous for his work on horror films The Beyond, Zombi 2 and more takes over, selecting an hour of musical inspirations.

Musical selections from the filmography of Parker Posey, dubbed "Queen of the Indies" starring in numerous independent films from the early 1990s onwards. Including sounds from Dazed & Confused, Flirt, Party Girl, The White Lotus and more. 
Selected and mixed by Florence Scott-Anderton.

nts1.n: NTS GUIDE TO: MUSIC FROM JAPAN’S CD-ERA ELECTRONIC UNDERGROUND (R)
nts1.d:
A journey through Japan’s quietly radical independent underground of the late ‘90s and early 2000s. Drawn from small-run CDs, obscure compilations, and deeply interconnected label networks, reflecting a moment where ambient, glitch, IDM, and experimental club sounds flourished into new forms — shaped by a generation of artists working across clubs, galleries, and record shops.
Created by Cameron Cullen
nts1.j: MUSIC FROM JAPAN’S CD-ERA ELECTRONIC UNDERGROUND

nts1.d: JG Wilkes plays an hour of eclectic and personal selections in memory of his friend and partner JD Twitch.
The breezy sound of the Canadian Riviera, from Mood Hut's Pender Street Steppers.

nts1.n: DANCE MUSIC SHOW W/ BELL TOWERS (R)
nts1.d: Prolific producer + DJ from Melbourne, Australia - Bell Towers presents his Dance Music Show.
Regular techno, electro, and house missives from the Against Interpretation labelhead and powerhouse-club selector Courtesy…

nts1.n: THE EXHIBITION HOUR W/ DAZEGXD & TIM REAPER (R)
nts1.d: Brooklyn, NY born and based DJ and record producer Dazegxd spends an hour on the NTS waves with an exhibition of his signature style - blending cuts dancy, deep, and downright classic from hip-hop to jungle.
Self-made underground rapper and model Cortisa Star shares an hour of selections from iconic club and drill tracks to bass-heavy picks from her own catalogue.
South Korean hyperpop pioneer Effie - credited with launching Korea’s first Sad Girl movement - joins NTS following the release of her debut album, ‘E’.

nts1.n: HOW WE BE W/ KOSLOWS & MH -(R)
nts1.d: Producers and DJs koslows & mh mark the release of their new EP with an hour of unreleased tracks and dancehall classics and tropical ambient sounds.

nts1.n: UNITED IN FLAMES W/ OKLOU & MALIBU (R)
nts1.d:
Malibu is a French electronic musician whose work sails between ambient and ethereal music.
Forever inspired by soft reverbed vocals and melodious chord progressions, Malibu’s music is an immersive nostalgic journey in a sea of synthetic strings and choirs.

nts1.n: NTS GUIDE TO: MID-WESTERN '90S SPACE & POST ROCK (R)
BLUE SCREEN W/ AMAR - EFFY STONEM'S IPOD (R)
THE CURE TAKEOVER W/ ROBERT SMITH (R)

nts2.n: Hour of the Wolf w/ Coco Lova
nts2.d:
A mix inspired by the hour of the wolf. The expression comes from the
Nordic folklore and refers to the time before dawn - a space of
unconsciousness, obscurity, and vivid dreams. The selection moves through
ambient and electronic soundscapes, with traces of folk.

nts2.n: WALKING FOR PEACE OF MIND W/ BOLD G
nts2.d: Imagine this: you walk through the city and let these songs come to you like intrusive thoughts — fragments of peace, mental noise, and everything in between.

The Doukhobors are a pacifist Christian movement. They immigrated to Canada in 1899, fleeing persecution for their pacifist beliefs in the Russian Empire. This is a mix of their traditional a capella choral singing, rarely available online, reflecting their history and enduring call for peace.

nts2.n: PEACE, LOVE AND UNITY W/ AUSTIN MOULTON
nts2.d: The show features rare groove, gospel and soul tracks promoting the core message of ‘Love, Peace and Unity’. This is music with a message that is just as pertinent today as it was when these songs were released in the 1970s and 80’s.

Seeking peace and refuge in the depths of soundcloud with a dive into the sound design-centric world of Botanica. The movement's whimsical, sparkling sound design is summoned into the real world with pairings from contemporary classical and other experimental musics in this lichen-esque mix.

Some of my favourite tracks to listen to when my cortisol levels are too high. Taking you on a semi-spiritual musical journey to help find some semblance of inner peace. Listen to while meditating, ruminating, or when you're in need of a break from the complicated outside world.

Exploring the vigilance required to remain outside the military industrial complex. Tempo shifts reveal peace as its own form of strength. Celebrating Catherine Connolly, Ireland's newly elected president, who reclaims neutrality as a deliberate act of peace.

nts2.n: Peace for JD Twitch w/ CLAIR
nts2.d:
Peace for Keith 
For JD Twitch and our pals. Some compositions Keith liked, some pieces he wouldn’t have the chance to know, something he made under a secret pseudonym. Rest easy old friend, we love you forever.
Photo by Brian Sweeney.
Like a sweet memory, happy phone call, or the comfort of mum's hug, this mix represents peace in all its forms. Sounds, scripts, and dreamy guitar brought to you by Megan Habashi.

nts2.n: Con el corazón pa’ ti w/ jojokausik
nts2.d: Describir la paz con palabras es un desafío, pero la música puede trazar su mapa emocional. Este mix es mi humilde intento de abrazar sus múltiples facetas: la calma que serena, el amor que abriga, la nostalgia que reconcilia y la esperanza que ilumina. Una ofrenda sónica que viaja, directa y sinceramente, hacia tu corazón.

nts2.n: Peace Like a River w/ Southern Proletariat Music Company
nts2.d: Take it from two water signs: If water and soil hold memory, then peace can be found in the riverbed. Southern Proletariat Music Company offers an hourlong mix of peace-on-earth renderings in the fruitful music of our upbringings and influences from the general Afro-American perspective. Consider this ruminating mix as a sonic earthenware for those seeking an inner sanctum for spiritual regeneration with a dash of hope for today, tomorrow and thereafter.

nts2.n: You Can Never Go Home w/ Izze
nts2.d: These are songs for a transitional period, maybe one where peace was chosen instead of found. The end of a journey where the train ride home feels melancholic and cathartic.

The glitchy blips and bops of Indietronica always remind me of how organic music is and how rhythm and melody shape our lives without us realizing. Enjoy this one hour Indietronica mix to find peace in knowing that music is everywhere around us ☆
For when you need to soften the edges.

subtle.d:
DJ & Producer, B-Say has been a Subtle resident DJ for over 3 years.

His radio shows tend to focus on the 140 bass music scene and aims to showcase unreleased/forthcoming music from upcoming artists, as well as premiering his own unreleased material. 

More recently B-Say has ventured out from solely DJ'ing Dubstep, with his bi-monthly 'Dub & Steppers Show' which he uses to premier his own productions.

Slick is a London-based Producer and DJ combining the sounds of Grime and Drill.
Expect sets to span from sparse wave and weightless to classic NY and UK Drill, with everything in between
J:KENZO is a producer and record label owner (Artikal Music & Lion Charge) from the UK. Known for his minimalistic dark tribal sound in the both the dubstep and drum and bass scenes since 2006.

subtle.n: Pattern Recognition w/ R A L L Y
Mid Morning Matters w/ Alfie Danger
Taking the Peel w/ Badly Drawn Banana

subtle.d:
DJ and radio producer TILDA will be live from the studio to kick off your weekend. She’ll cover all corners of electronic music as well as showcasing unmissable new tracks & chatting about motives for the weekend. 

Each month TILDA will be closing the show with a signature mix.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Following his widely acclaimed breakout moment winning the 2013 DMC World Online Championships, Jon1st quickly built an international reputation as a ‘DJ’s DJ’. Not only proving himself as one of the world’s most diverse and musical turntablists, Jon also established himself as an on the pulse club DJ mixing across the alternative bass music spectrum and as an in demand live performer around the world, as well as recording acclaimed guest mixes for everyone from DJ Mag to Boiler Room to Ninja Tune’s Solid Steel to Mary Anne Hobbs to Keep Hush.

Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
